message.content: Cornus drummondii is a species of flowering plant that belongs to the family Cornaceae. This tree or shrub can grow up to 20 feet tall with a trunk diameter of about 6 inches. The bark of Cornus drummondii is gray or brown in color and has a smooth texture. The leaves of this plant are oval-shaped and have an alternate arrangement. They are dark green in color and have a smooth texture with prominent veins. Cornus drummondii produces clusters of small white flowers in the spring, followed by small blue-black fruit in the summer. This plant is commonly used in landscaping and can be found in gardens, parks, and along roadsides.
